The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 India, Pak in same group 

New Delhi: Arch-rivals India and Pakistan have been clubbed together in one group for the mens hockey tournament at the Commonwealth Games in Melbourne scheduled for March next year. 

The two giants, along with Malaysia, have found place in group B of the ten-nation event. South Africa and Trinidad and Tobago are the other two countries of the group. 

Hosts and Olympic champions Australia, New Zealand, England, Canada and Australia are in group A. 

In the womens, India finds itself in group A along with Australia, Malaysia, South Africa and Nigeria. (PTI) 




